org.safs.cukes.ai.selenium

Class AISearchBase

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.safs.SAFSPlus
      • org.safs.selenium.webdriver.SeleniumPlus
        • org.safs.cukes.ai.selenium.AISearchBase
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AIComponent, AIDebugActions

    public class AISearchBase
extends SeleniumPlus
    The base class on which many AI Search Algorithms will subclass.

    There can be no invokable step definition methods in this class since no true step definition file is allowed to be extended.

    To execute a Cucumber test based on this class:

    1. Your SeleniumPlus test class might EXTEND this AISearchBase class,
    2. That subclass must implement/override the SeleniumPlus.runTest() method,
    3. the runTest() method will call the runCukesTest(String, String) method with appropriate glue and feature file parameters.

    Alternatively, you might be able to call the static runCukesTest(String, String) method from anywhere to run one or more Cucumber invocations.

    The following JARs must be in the JVM CLASSPATH for such a Unit test invocation. This is the same as any other SeleniumPlus test invocation: 

             pathTo/yourClasses/bin or yourTest.jar,
         pathTo/seleniumplus.jar,
         pathTo/JSTAFEmbedded.jar, (or JSTAF.jar if using STAF and other external tools or engines.)
    Then, you can execute this test with an invocation similar to: 
             java -cp %CLASSPATH% td.testcases.stepdefs.AISearchBase
    See Also:
    SeleniumPlus.main(java.lang.String[]), SAFSPlus.runTest(), runCukesTest(String, String)

      • findSelectableItemFromText

        public org.openqa.selenium.WebElement findSelectableItemFromText(java.lang.String text)
        Find the first WebElement whose text matches the provided text.
        The search will be tried on each frame until we find the first matched element.
        Note:
        1. Once this method is done, we should have switched to a certain frame.
        2. If substring matches are enabled, then we will also attempt partial substring matches.
        3. If the search is slow, this might be caused by the timeout, we can accelerate by calling AIMiscActions.do_not_wait_if_a_component_is_not_ready().
        Parameters:
        text - String
        Returns:
        WebElement matching requested text or null if not found.
        See Also:
        AIMiscActions.accept_partial_text_matches(), AIMiscActions.deny_partial_text_matches(), AIMiscActions.do_not_wait_if_a_component_is_not_ready()

      • deduceTestFile

        protected java.io.File deduceTestFile(java.lang.String filename)
                               throws SAFSException
        Deduce the absolute full path test-relative file.
        Parameters:
        filename, - String, the test/actual file name. If there are any File.separators in the relative path then the path is actually considered relative to the Datapool directory unless it does not exist, or is already an absolute file path.

        If a relative directory path does not exist relative to the Datapool directory then the final path will be relative to the Project directory.

        If it is an absolute path, and contains a root path that includes the Bench directory, then the file will be converted to a comparable relative path off the Test directory.

        Returns:
        File, the absolute full path test file.
        Throws:
        SAFSException
        See Also:
        FileUtilities.deduceFile(String, int, RuntimeDataInterface)

      • runCukesTest

        public static void runCukesTest(java.lang.String features)
                         throws java.lang.Throwable
        Starts a Cucumber Runtime and executes Cucumber test(s) with the default step definitions in package DEFAULT_SEPLUS_AI_DEFINITIONS. Examples:
        • Using the default Step Definition files defined in DEFAULT_SEPLUS_AI_DEFINITIONS, and locates the single AltSearchAI.feature file to runs that test in Cucumber.
          runCukesTest("./Tests/td/testcases/features/AltSearchAI.feature");
        • Using the default Step Definition files defined in DEFAULT_SEPLUS_AI_DEFINITIONS, and locates the ./resources/features directory to runs tests based on the feature files found there.
          runCukesTest("./resources/features");
        Parameters:
        features - String, the path to the directory of feature files, or the specific feature file to run.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Throwable

      • runCukesTest

        public static void runCukesTest(java.lang.String glue,
                                java.lang.String features)
                         throws java.lang.Throwable
        Starts a Cucumber Runtime and executes Cucumber test(s) with the glue and feature file specs provided.

        Examples:

            runCukesTest( "td", "./Tests/td/testcases/features/AltSearchAI.feature");
          Searches the "td" Java package and all subpackages for usable Step Definition files.
          Locates the single AltSearchAI.feature file and runs that test in Cucumber.

            runCukesTest( "org.mine.steps", "./resources/features");
          Searches the "org.mine.steps" Java package and all subpackages for usable Step Definition files.
          Locates the ./resources/features directory and runs tests based on the feature files found there.

        Step Definition files are sought using the calling Thread's context ClassLoader.
        Parameters:
        glue - String, the Java package root containing the Java Step Definition files to use.
        features - String, the path to the directory of feature files, or the specific feature file to run.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Throwable
        See Also:
        java.lang.Thread#getContextClassLoader()}

      • runCukesTest

        public static void runCukesTest(java.lang.String features,
                                java.lang.String... glues)
                         throws java.lang.Throwable
        Starts a Cucumber Runtime and executes Cucumber test(s) with the glues and feature file specs provided.

        Examples:

            runCukesTest("./Tests/td/testcases/features/AltSearchAI.feature", "td", "org.mine.steps");
          Searches the "td" and "org.mine.steps" Java packages and all subpackages for usable Step Definition files.
          Locates the single AltSearchAI.feature file and runs that test in Cucumber.

            runCukesTest("./resources/features", "td", "org.mine.steps");
          Searches the "td" and "org.mine.steps" Java packages and all subpackages for usable Step Definition files.
          Locates the ./resources/features directory and runs tests based on the feature files found there.

        Step Definition files are sought using the calling Thread's context ClassLoader.
        Parameters:
        features - String, the path to the directory of feature files, or the specific feature file to run.
        glues - String[], the Java packages containing the Java Step Definition files to use.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Throwable
        See Also:
        java.lang.Thread#getContextClassLoader()}
